INTRODUCTION
This document is the Work Instruction (WI) for Document Change Request
PURPOSE
This WI defines the steps that are followed to implement a change to a controlled
document
SCOPE
The WI applies to the QMSrs Tool set that accompanies this WI

DOCUMENT CHANGE REQUEST WORK I NSTRUCTION
APPROVE DCR
This section explains how to approve a DCR
To approve a DCR:
 Go to Document Change Request section in the QMS.
 Select ‘Approve DCR'.
 Only DCRs that need your approval will appear to you.
 Click on edit icon“ “beside the DCR that you want to add approval for (The
status of the DCR should be open).
 Click on 'Approval Details' tab then select the status of the approval from the
drop down list and enter the justification.
 Click on “Save “to save the amended data or “Cancel” to cancel the changes.
CREATE NEW DCR
This section explains how to create Document Change Request. Anyone in the
organisation who has access to the QMS can raise a DCR
To create new DCR:
 Go to Document Change Request section in the QMS
 Select “Create DCR”.
 Fill the mandatory fields with the red asterisk ‘*’ and any other fields you
have data for.

 Click on save icon “ ” to save changes that appears at the top of the
window.
DCR Entry Fields
Below are the fields to be completed when adding a DCR.
Field Name Description
DCR Details
Document No. Select the document No. from Popup menu that
appears when you click on search icon or enter the
number manually then click on "Enter" from the
keyboard
DCR Type Select the type from the drop-down list
Origination Date Select the origination date from the calendar
Document File URL Enter the link of the document in the following format:
http://www.google.com
Document File Insert the file of document to load it.
Document ID Select document ID from the drop-down list
Document Title Document Title will be display automatically
DCR Originator Select the originator from the drop down list.

DOCUMENT CHANGE REQUEST PROCESS
This section displays the flow of the process.
MANAGE DCR
In this section the user can edit a DCR, add approval members to DCR (when the
status of the DCR is open) or use the filter to search a DCR using varying criteria.
EDIT DCR
 Go to Document Change Request section in the QMS.
 Select ‘Manage DCR’.
 Click on edit icon“ “beside the DCR that you want to edit if the status of
the DCR is open.
 Make the necessary changes.
 Click on “Save “to save the amended data or “Cancel” to cancel the changes.
DCR Owner Select the owner from the drop down list.
Reason for change Enter the reason to support the DCR

ADDING APPROVAL MEMBERS
 Go to Document Change Request section in the QMS.
 Select ‘Manage DCR’.
 Click on edit icon“ “beside the DCR that you want to edit (if the status of
the DCR is open).
 Click on Approval Members tab then click on add icon“ “.
 Double click on 'Member 'field and select the name from the drop down list.
 Double click on 'Type' field and select the type from the drop down list.
 Click on “Save “to save the amended data or “Cancel” to cancel the changes.
* 'Approval Status' and 'Decision Details' fields will be filled later from DCR Approvals
section by the member whom you add and responsible for the decision.
DELETING APPROVAL MEMBERS

DCR ID DCR-1 Issue 1 Date: 1/9/2014 PAGE 8 of 10

 Go to Document Change Request section in the QMS.
 Select ‘Manage DCR’.
 Click on edit icon“ “beside the DCR that you want to edit (if the status of
the DCR is open).
 Click on Approval Members tab then click on delete icon“ “that is located
beside the member you want to delete.
 Click on “Save “to save the amended data or “Cancel” to cancel the changes.
SEARCH DCR
 Go to Document Change Request section in the QMS.
 Select ‘Manage DCR’.
 Click on filter icon “ “at the top of the window, then select the search
criteria.
 Fill the text field or select from the drop down list which depends on the
search criteria you choose.
 After finding the DCR, you can view and edit its details.
COMMUNICATION
Automatic email will be send to a predefined list of people as defined on email
templates

REPORTS
VI EW ALL DCR RECORDS
In this section the user can view all CCN with their status and details, also can use
the filter with its different search criteria to search for CCN
 Click on filter icon “ “at the top of the window, then select the search
criteria.
 Fill the text field or select from the drop down list which depends on the
search criteria you choose.
VI EW STATUS ANALYSIS
This section displays DCRs according to their status (open, closed, cancelled)) and the
user can filter the result for each month with a year period.
